Seon Ho, you need to check...

502
00:15:53,492 --> 00:15:54,831
- who's in our crew.
- Okay.

503
00:15:54,832 --> 00:15:56,161
We can't leave unless everyone is here.

504
00:15:56,162 --> 00:15:57,961
- Count them.
- Show us your faces.

505
00:15:57,962 --> 00:15:59,031
- Show us your faces.
- All right.

506
00:15:59,032 --> 00:16:00,032
- We'll start with him.
- Everyone.

507
00:16:00,033 --> 00:16:01,931
- One, two, three, four, five, six, - Yes.

508
00:16:01,932 --> 00:16:03,031
Seven, eight, nine.

509
00:16:03,032 --> 00:16:04,101
- There are nine of you.
- That's right.

510
00:16:04,102 --> 00:16:05,841
- Okay.
- Make sure to remember your number.

511
00:16:05,842 --> 00:16:06,842
- Okay.
- Okay.

512
00:16:07,472 --> 00:16:09,112
I wonder how much of a head start he has.

513
00:16:09,942 --> 00:16:11,782
DinDin is fast indeed.

514
00:16:12,012 --> 00:16:13,881
He's gotten more dangerous after his trip to Canada.

515
00:16:13,882 --> 00:16:15,411
He's disrupting our ecosystem.

516
00:16:15,412 --> 00:16:17,452
- He's Din-tria. We must get him.
- He's Din-tria.

517
00:16:17,922 --> 00:16:20,691
Gosh, if we lose, it will be so embarrassing.

518
00:16:20,692 --> 00:16:22,922
- Right. Yes.
- There are four of us.

519
00:16:23,022 --> 00:16:25,022
No. We were able to crack it once we tried.

520
00:16:25,222 --> 00:16:26,991
- We figured it out.
- Yes.

521
00:16:26,992 --> 00:16:29,192
Let me say this to boost our morale.

522
00:16:29,392 --> 00:16:33,202
Guess where this kind of question shows up a lot.

523
00:16:33,472 --> 00:16:35,401
- Escape rooms.
- Right.

524
00:16:35,402 --> 00:16:36,531
What must mice do?

525
00:16:36,532 --> 00:16:37,901
- They must escape rooms.
- That's right.

526
00:16:37,902 --> 00:16:39,671
- That's the thing with mice.
- They look for holes.

527
00:16:39,672 --> 00:16:41,641
It's in their instincts to escape.

528
00:16:41,642 --> 00:16:43,811
So he cleverly figured out the first question. You know?

529
00:16:43,812 --> 00:16:44,812
- I see.
- Yes.

530
00:16:44,813 --> 00:16:47,212
So he was bound to beat us with this question.

531
00:16:47,312 --> 00:16:49,552
- But you were on that show.
- What?

532
00:16:50,022 --> 00:16:51,152
- "Great Escape?"
- Yes.

533
00:16:51,522 --> 00:16:52,621
- What about it?
- You must be good at this.

534
00:16:52,622 --> 00:16:54,302
- This is what they do on the show.
- Yes.

535
00:16:54,722 --> 00:16:55,992
But I wasn't good at this.

536
00:16:57,492 --> 00:16:58,822
(Laughing)

537
00:16:59,192 --> 00:17:00,692
Don't attack your teammate now.

538
00:17:02,232 --> 00:17:04,631
- Right. We must be a strong team.
- Yes.

539
00:17:04,632 --> 00:17:06,672
- Yes. We must work together.
- We need to do that.

540
00:17:07,202 --> 00:17:10,172
I should tell you that I usually go up against KAIST graduates.

541
00:17:11,102 --> 00:17:12,841
Seon Ho, we got lucky with this.

542
00:17:12,842 --> 00:17:13,911
(At that moment, a siren suddenly goes off.)

543
00:17:13,912 --> 00:17:15,352
- What's this sound?
- What is this?

544
00:17:15,542 --> 00:17:17,581
(Catch the mouse, squeak, squeak.)

545
00:17:17,582 --> 00:17:18,782
Welcome, everyone.

546
00:17:19,342 --> 00:17:23,012
This bus is off to catch a mouse.

547
00:17:23,522 --> 00:17:26,892
This mouse that just turned up is a very sly one.

548
00:17:27,422 --> 00:17:29,251
- We must become one.
- Gosh.

549
00:17:29,252 --> 00:17:31,461
I'd appreciate it if you could help us catch the mouse.

550
00:17:31,462 --> 00:17:32,868
Let's start with the right side. Go.

551
00:17:32,892 --> 00:17:34,832
- Right. Left.
- Catch the mouse

552
00:17:35,132 --> 00:17:38,162
(Catch the mouse)

553
00:17:38,602 --> 00:17:40,831
(Let's boost our teamwork.)

554
00:17:40,832 --> 00:17:41,871
Faster!

555
00:17:41,872 --> 00:17:44,042
(This time, let's increase the speed.)

556
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:46,171
- Catch the mouse - Catch the mouse

557
00:17:46,172 --> 00:17:47,371
Show your front teeth.

558
00:17:47,372 --> 00:17:48,471
(Boosting their morale)

559
00:17:48,472 --> 00:17:49,472
I'm tired now.

560
00:17:49,473 --> 00:17:52,381
- Here we go.
- Let's go!

561
00:17:52,382 --> 00:17:53,382
- Let's go!
- That was great.

562
00:17:53,383 --> 00:17:55,282
Everyone, make some noise!

563
00:17:55,982 --> 00:17:58,022
(With this momentum, he will be a mouse in a trap.)

564
00:17:58,082 --> 00:17:59,852
- Let's corner him!
- Let's corner him.

565
00:18:00,022 --> 00:18:02,191
How about Team Mouse Hunters?

566
00:18:02,192 --> 00:18:03,662
- Isn't that cute?
- Yes.

567
00:18:04,562 --> 00:18:07,392
(Meanwhile, what is their target, Mouse DinDin, up to?)

568
00:18:07,532 --> 00:18:10,232
I could've figured it out in one second.

569
00:18:11,262 --> 00:18:14,032
But I was still sleepy.

570
00:18:14,332 --> 00:18:15,372
That's a bummer.

571
00:18:16,372 --> 00:18:19,142
I hope there aren't any questions about English. Seriously.

572
00:18:21,042 --> 00:18:24,182
I spoke in English a lot when I went to Canada for the shoot.

573
00:18:24,782 --> 00:18:26,742
The staff felt uncomfortable around me afterward.

574
00:18:28,112 --> 00:18:29,351
(Thus began...)

575
00:18:29,352 --> 00:18:31,522
Whether I was in school or wherever I went,

576
00:18:32,082 --> 00:18:33,952
no one had called me stupid.

577
00:18:34,292 --> 00:18:37,461
My teachers commented that I was clever.

578
00:18:37,462 --> 00:18:39,192
They always said that to me.

579
00:18:39,592 --> 00:18:42,532
I'm going to beat them today. It will be a complete victory.

580
00:18:42,692 --> 00:18:45,601
Sometime around next year, we could do an episode...

581
00:18:45,602 --> 00:18:47,632
to show how much they improved.

582
00:18:48,972 --> 00:18:51,372
So I'm thinking about destroying them today.

583
00:18:52,202 --> 00:18:53,811
My gosh. The weather is great.

584
00:18:53,812 --> 00:18:55,292
(He takes time to enjoy the weather.)

585
00:18:55,742 --> 00:18:56,781
Right.

586
00:18:56,782 --> 00:18:58,441
(The sky is clear without a single cloud.)

587
00:18:58,442 --> 00:18:59,811
I wonder what they're doing.

588
00:18:59,812 --> 00:19:01,881
I'm a bit lonely because it's just me here.

589
00:19:01,882 --> 00:19:03,381
(Does he miss the members?)

590
00:19:03,382 --> 00:19:05,062
So this is the sad part of being a genius.

591
00:19:05,652 --> 00:19:07,722
Beethoven, Einstein, and other geniuses...

592
00:19:08,322 --> 00:19:09,752
struggled with loneliness.

593
00:19:10,292 --> 00:19:12,522
Could you call them?

594
00:19:12,922 --> 00:19:13,961
Call them?

595
00:19:13,962 --> 00:19:16,492
(The lonely genius, DinDin, tries to call them.)

596
00:19:16,632 --> 00:19:17,932
- Hey.
- Hello.

597
00:19:18,862 --> 00:19:20,731
I wanted to ask you where you were.

598
00:19:20,732 --> 00:19:22,708
I wanted to ask you whether I should wait for you...

599
00:19:22,732 --> 00:19:24,471
or leave after solving the question.

600
00:19:24,472 --> 00:19:26,441
You ought to hurry up.

601
00:19:26,442 --> 00:19:27,871
- Should I just go?
- Yes.

602
00:19:27,872 --> 00:19:30,882
We're right up on your tail. So be careful.

603
00:19:30,942 --> 00:19:32,611
Really? Where are you now?

604
00:19:32,612 --> 00:19:33,612
(Mistrustful)

605
00:19:33,613 --> 00:19:35,151
- Do you want to know where we are?
- Yes.

606
00:19:35,152 --> 00:19:38,252
You're on Lane Two now.

607
00:19:39,122 --> 00:19:40,122
What?

608
00:19:40,887 --> 00:19:43,997
You're on Lane Two now.

609
00:19:44,216 --> 00:19:45,216
What?

610
00:19:46,918 --> 00:19:50,027
(DinDin is indeed on Lane 2.)

611
00:19:50,028 --> 00:19:51,158
Be careful.

612
00:19:51,558 --> 00:19:54,558
Mice are bound to be caught by cats.

613
00:19:54,758 --> 00:19:55,797
What?

614
00:19:55,798 --> 00:19:56,997
(Hanging up)

615
00:19:56,998 --> 00:19:58,927
He knew I was on Lane Two?

616
00:19:58,928 --> 00:20:00,597
(Are they right behind me?)

617
00:20:00,598 --> 00:20:01,738
They can see me?

618
00:20:03,168 --> 00:20:04,237
What's this?

619
00:20:04,238 --> 00:20:06,837
(Se Yoon hangs up the phone after a mysterious comment.)

620
00:20:06,838 --> 00:20:07,978
Can they see me?

621
00:20:08,738 --> 00:20:09,908
How did they know?

622
00:20:11,078 --> 00:20:13,054
(It was when he was heading out from the KBS building.)

623
00:20:13,078 --> 00:20:15,847
(After mocking the members, )

624
00:20:15,848 --> 00:20:16,917
(he took Seogang Bridge and got on the Gangbyeon Highway.)

625
00:20:16,918 --> 00:20:21,388
(DinDin, Seogang Bridge, Mapo Bridge)

626
00:20:21,688 --> 00:20:22,857
(Team Mouse Hunters)

627
00:20:22,858 --> 00:20:25,257
(Take Mapo Bridge.)

628
00:20:25,258 --> 00:20:26,287
(Mouse Hunters, DinDin)

629
00:20:26,288 --> 00:20:32,468
(On the other hand, Mouse Hunters took Mapo Bridge.)

630
00:20:32,998 --> 00:20:35,267
(That's how they ended up on the Gangbyeon Highway...)

631
00:20:35,268 --> 00:20:37,508
(around the same time.)

632
00:20:38,268 --> 00:20:40,638
That can't be DinDin's car, right? It's the same model.

633
00:20:40,908 --> 00:20:42,607
- I saw him in a white Casper.
- Yes.

634
00:20:42,608 --> 00:20:44,578
- Did anyone catch the plate number?
- No.

635
00:20:44,778 --> 00:20:46,247
- Where's the Casper?
- It's right in front of us.

636
00:20:46,248 --> 00:20:48,217
- It's at your two o'clock.
- That can't be his car.

637
00:20:48,218 --> 00:20:49,948
(No way. That can't be his car.)

638
00:20:53,018 --> 00:20:54,917
I do think that's DinDin's car.

639
00:20:54,918 --> 00:20:56,358
- What? Really?
- For real?

640
00:20:56,428 --> 00:20:58,387
- He crossed over.
- Really?

641
00:20:58,388 --> 00:20:59,957
- There was traffic.
- We caught up.

642
00:20:59,958 --> 00:21:01,258
We caught up. Let's get him.

643
00:21:01,428 --> 00:21:02,697
- This one?
- Watch the road.

644
00:21:02,698 --> 00:21:03,797
Don't force it.

645
00:21:03,798 --> 00:21:05,497
Catch the mouse

646
00:21:05,498 --> 00:21:07,368
- Squeak - I'll make sure we're safe.

647
00:21:07,568 --> 00:21:09,198
He's barely ahead of us then.

648
00:21:09,498 --> 00:21:11,367
He must be an awful driver. We basically caught up with him.

649
00:21:11,368 --> 00:21:13,278
- He's not a good driver.
- Exactly.

650
00:21:13,808 --> 00:21:15,378
He didn't make it far.

651
00:21:15,778 --> 00:21:19,818
Now that we caught up, we didn't lose the first game.

652
00:21:19,918 --> 00:21:21,277
Anything could happen now.

653
00:21:21,278 --> 00:21:23,488
We'll keep cornering the mouse.

654
00:21:23,818 --> 00:21:25,688
(DinDin is closer than they expected.)

655
00:21:26,048 --> 00:21:27,487
(Bursting into laughter)

656
00:21:27,488 --> 00:21:28,517
Detective Lee.

657
00:21:28,518 --> 00:21:30,388
Let's go and catch the mouse.

658
00:21:31,358 --> 00:21:32,358
That's right.

659
00:21:32,359 --> 00:21:34,358
Catch. I caught the mouse.

660
00:21:34,428 --> 00:21:36,498
(I caught the mouse)

661
00:21:37,428 --> 00:21:40,498
(Hope is springing up.)

662
00:21:42,198 --> 00:21:44,507
I went there to tease them and got stuck in traffic.

663
00:21:44,508 --> 00:21:46,338
(I shouldn't have gone there to tease them.)

664
00:21:47,178 --> 00:21:48,738
It's all right.

665
00:21:50,308 --> 00:21:52,347
(Looking far from okay)

666
00:21:52,348 --> 00:21:53,947
It was the least I could do.

667
00:21:53,948 --> 00:21:55,718
(He tries to comfort himself.)

668
00:21:55,848 --> 00:21:58,918
I'll get ahead again by solving questions.

669
00:22:00,418 --> 00:22:02,058
There might not be questions.

670
00:22:02,288 --> 00:22:03,288
That's true.

671
00:22:03,458 --> 00:22:06,727
(It might not require thinking.)

672
00:22:06,728 --> 00:22:08,957
If it isn't a question, it'd be hard to tell.

673
00:22:08,958 --> 00:22:09,967
(He's getting more anxious.)

674
00:22:09,968 --> 00:22:11,867
- What should I...
- Stop. He's up ahead.

675
00:22:11,868 --> 00:22:13,937
(Stop. He's up ahead.)

676
00:22:13,938 --> 00:22:15,778
Hold on. Does the plate number start with two?

677
00:22:15,898 --> 00:22:17,407
- Wait a minute.
- Slow down.

678
00:22:17,408 --> 00:22:18,608
- We caught him.
- That's him.

679
00:22:18,868 --> 00:22:19,907
- We caught him.
- We caught him.

680
00:22:19,908 --> 00:22:22,138
We caught him.

681
00:22:22,378 --> 00:22:23,578
The one who catches...

682
00:22:23,748 --> 00:22:25,677
(Could it be them?)

683
00:22:25,678 --> 00:22:26,748
Are they here already?

684
00:22:27,878 --> 00:22:28,878
(Laughing)

685
00:22:29,448 --> 00:22:30,518
What?

686
00:22:31,418 --> 00:22:34,388
(Mouse Hunters pass by DinDin while laughing.)

687
00:22:34,988 --> 00:22:39,358
(He gets overtaken right before his eyes.)

688
00:22:39,758 --> 00:22:40,927
I knew this would happen.

689
00:22:40,928 --> 00:22:42,257
(Sighing)

690
00:22:42,258 --> 00:22:44,467
I tried to beat them in driving.

691
00:22:44,468 --> 00:22:45,498
(He underestimated them.)

692
00:22:45,728 --> 00:22:47,798
(Meanwhile, Mouse Hunters who overtook DinDin)

693
00:22:48,498 --> 00:22:49,767
- Gosh, we caught him.
- We did.

694
00:22:49,768 --> 00:22:51,207
He's a bad driver.

695
00:22:51,208 --> 00:22:52,308
We caught him.

696
00:22:53,038 --> 00:22:54,208
We caught that little mouse.

697
00:22:54,638 --> 00:22:56,408
Yes. You're doing well, Detective Lee.

698
00:22:56,708 --> 00:22:58,777
It's true. We may not be clever,

699
00:22:58,778 --> 00:23:00,378
but we catch up with physical abilities.

700
00:23:00,718 --> 00:23:02,077
DinDin is behind us.

701
00:23:02,078 --> 00:23:03,424
(A proud license holder for driving large vehicles)

702
00:23:03,448 --> 00:23:05,617
We have two minutes left. Get ready to go.

703
00:23:05,618 --> 00:23:06,917
- Okay.
- Are we there already?

704
00:23:06,918 --> 00:23:08,387
Yes, we're almost there.

705
00:23:08,388 --> 00:23:10,557
- Now...
- Should I go into the parking lot?

706
00:23:10,558 --> 00:23:12,718
Didn't I tell you that the flowers are beautiful here?

707
00:23:13,088 --> 00:23:16,158
(They arrived almost at the same time.)

708
00:23:16,428 --> 00:23:18,167
- It's spacious.
- Go there directly.

709
00:23:18,168 --> 00:23:19,868
- Please get out of the car.
- Get out!

710
00:23:19,968 --> 00:23:22,097
Let's give the mouse a minute to run.

711
00:23:22,098 --> 00:23:24,208
There he is. He's passing us.

712
00:23:24,768 --> 00:23:26,368
- After arriving...
- Where is he going?

713
00:23:26,438 --> 00:23:28,338
This is it. I'm getting out.

714
00:23:28,508 --> 00:23:30,408
(A parking lot for small cars)

715
00:23:32,278 --> 00:23:33,547
(DinDin gets out after parking quickly.)

716
00:23:33,548 --> 00:23:34,578
Those fools.

717
00:23:35,748 --> 00:23:38,588
Those fools parked the car over there after getting here early.

718
00:23:38,888 --> 00:23:40,017
(DinDin, Mouse Hunters)

719
00:23:40,018 --> 00:23:42,788
(DinDin runs after parking right in front of the mission location.)

720
00:23:43,728 --> 00:23:45,368
(DinDin arrives at the mission location.)

721
00:23:45,458 --> 00:23:46,578
(Checking the opponent team)

722
00:23:46,658 --> 00:23:48,898
Please get out. We're here.

723
00:23:49,028 --> 00:23:50,467
- Get out.
- Please get out.

724
00:23:50,468 --> 00:23:51,728
- Go there directly.
- Get out.

725
00:23:51,798 --> 00:23:52,798
(Mouse Hunters run in a hurry.)

726
00:23:52,799 --> 00:23:54,497
- Run!
- Run.

727
00:23:54,498 --> 00:23:56,198
Run. We have to go there fast.

728
00:23:56,498 --> 00:23:57,767
What's the mission?

729
00:23:57,768 --> 00:23:59,488
The mission at Namyangju Hangang Park is...

730
00:24:00,008 --> 00:24:01,438
Reading Colors Fast.

731
00:24:02,708 --> 00:24:05,348
You must read the color of the text...

732
00:24:05,878 --> 00:24:07,277
and not the text itself to succeed.

733
00:24:07,278 --> 00:24:08,477
(Read accurately within 20 seconds to succeed.)

734
00:24:08,478 --> 00:24:10,888
If you fail, drink a cup...

735
00:24:11,248 --> 00:24:13,368
of sophora root tea that will help refresh your mind.

736
00:24:13,558 --> 00:24:15,088
- Then you can try again.
- Okay.

737
00:24:16,828 --> 00:24:19,204
(Meanwhile, Mouse Hunters arrive at the mission location also.)

738
00:24:19,228 --> 00:24:20,634
What's that? Is it something to drink?

739
00:24:20,658 --> 00:24:21,927
It must be a random game.

740
00:24:21,928 --> 00:24:23,098
Hurry up over here.

741
00:24:23,428 --> 00:24:24,898
All right. Here's the question.

742
00:24:25,398 --> 00:24:27,497
You must read the color of the text and not the text itself.

743
00:24:27,498 --> 00:24:28,638
- I know.
- The color?

744
00:24:28,768 --> 00:24:30,037
- We have to read the color.
- Okay.

745
00:24:30,038 --> 00:24:31,467
- Don't read the text.
- All right.

746
00:24:31,468 --> 00:24:33,408
If "yellow" is written in red,

747
00:24:33,678 --> 00:24:35,008
you must say red. No, yellow.

748
00:24:35,508 --> 00:24:36,677
Only look at the color.

749
00:24:36,678 --> 00:24:38,177
(He's confused even before starting.)

750
00:24:38,178 --> 00:24:40,578
I'll start the mission.

751
00:24:41,018 --> 00:24:42,647
Start.

752
00:24:42,648 --> 00:24:44,317
(The mission starts.)

753
00:24:44,318 --> 00:24:47,058
Green, red, blue, red, yellow.

754
00:24:47,288 --> 00:24:48,317
(Hesitating)

755
00:24:48,318 --> 00:24:49,458
What's that?

756
00:24:50,188 --> 00:24:51,188
(Shouting)

757
00:24:52,858 --> 00:24:55,428
(Joon is causing disruption.)

758
00:24:55,858 --> 00:24:59,298
Black, blue, purple, red, black, green.

759
