1239
00:41:13,238 --> 00:41:14,478
But my hands are dirty.

1240
00:41:14,508 --> 00:41:15,778
My goodness.

1241
00:41:16,278 --> 00:41:17,707
Would you like some?

1242
00:41:17,708 --> 00:41:19,207
Yes, is it okay?

1243
00:41:19,208 --> 00:41:20,677
(Se Yoon gets a bite successfully.)

1244
00:41:20,678 --> 00:41:23,418
- Gosh, it's hot.
- I'm sorry.

1245
00:41:23,478 --> 00:41:24,647
Oh, no.

1246
00:41:24,648 --> 00:41:26,188
Thank you.

1247
00:41:27,818 --> 00:41:29,688
- I didn't even have to ask for it.
- Right.

1248
00:41:29,788 --> 00:41:31,627
- I was feeling the same way.
- Thank you.

1249
00:41:31,628 --> 00:41:33,887
- This is a small gift for you.
- That's okay.

1250
00:41:33,888 --> 00:41:34,997
It's a gift. Please receive it.

1251
00:41:34,998 --> 00:41:36,327
- Thank you so much.
- No problem.

1252
00:41:36,328 --> 00:41:38,397
- Thank you for this.
- Thank you. You're a lifesaver.

1253
00:41:38,398 --> 00:41:39,897
- You're welcome.
- Thank you so much.

1254
00:41:39,898 --> 00:41:41,137
(Jong Min is the last one of Mouse Hunters to finish the mission.)

1255
00:41:41,138 --> 00:41:42,458
I'm done. Have they all finished?

1256
00:41:43,138 --> 00:41:44,138
When did they finish?

1257
00:41:44,139 --> 00:41:45,544
(Se Yoon runs to help the other members.)

1258
00:41:45,568 --> 00:41:46,868
- Hello.
- Hello.

1259
00:41:47,578 --> 00:41:49,307
Hasn't the customer picked up the tteokbokki yet?

1260
00:41:49,308 --> 00:41:50,737
No, the customer hasn't picked it up.

1261
00:41:50,738 --> 00:41:52,547
I hope he or she picks it up soon.

1262
00:41:52,548 --> 00:41:53,724
(Jong Min's one-bite mission is tteokbokki.)

1263
00:41:53,748 --> 00:41:55,947
(Have you ever seen Kim hanging around the tteokbokki stand, )

1264
00:41:55,948 --> 00:41:57,617
(looking for someone to give him a bite?)

1265
00:41:57,618 --> 00:41:59,138
Why hasn't he or she picked it up yet?

1266
00:42:03,988 --> 00:42:06,428
(He found the owner of the tteokbokki.)

1267
00:42:06,658 --> 00:42:08,898
(Jong Min heads toward her to do the mission.)

1268
00:42:08,958 --> 00:42:11,798
(Lurking around)

1269
00:42:12,128 --> 00:42:13,298
Hello.

1270
00:42:14,028 --> 00:42:17,197
May I speak to you for a moment?

1271
00:42:17,198 --> 00:42:18,598
- Yes.
- Is it okay if we film you?

1272
00:42:20,438 --> 00:42:21,918
Are you going to eat that tteokbokki?

1273
00:42:22,078 --> 00:42:23,837
- Yes.
- No, we won't eat it.

1274
00:42:23,838 --> 00:42:24,948
You won't eat it?

1275
00:42:25,078 --> 00:42:26,947
They left with the tteokbokki to avoid sharing it with me.

1276
00:42:26,948 --> 00:42:29,247
(Shocked)

1277
00:42:29,248 --> 00:42:30,248
What should I do?

1278
00:42:30,418 --> 00:42:31,847
A sausage? Is this a corn dog?

1279
00:42:31,848 --> 00:42:34,088
(Meanwhile, DinDin is trying to get a bite of corn dog.)

1280
00:42:34,558 --> 00:42:36,188
(Please give me a bite.)

1281
00:42:39,588 --> 00:42:42,358
So he was asking for a bite when he asked what it was.

1282
00:42:43,858 --> 00:42:45,468
It's so delicious.

1283
00:42:45,868 --> 00:42:46,997
Success.

1284
00:42:46,998 --> 00:42:48,767
(DinDin successfully completed his one-bite mission.)

1285
00:42:48,768 --> 00:42:49,837
- What is it?
- Here you go.

1286
00:42:49,838 --> 00:42:51,437
(He obtains the hint on the next location.)

1287
00:42:51,438 --> 00:42:53,707
- Shall I buy you a new one?
- No, that's okay.

1288
00:42:53,708 --> 00:42:55,877
- How about some drinks?
- That's okay.

1289
00:42:55,878 --> 00:42:58,077
- Can you get us some coffee?
- Coffee? All right.

1290
00:42:58,078 --> 00:42:59,477
- This is a token of gratitude.
- We'll be on TV.

1291
00:42:59,478 --> 00:43:01,378
(Thank you for helping me.)

1292
00:43:01,448 --> 00:43:02,778
Oh, my. Mr. Kim Jong Min is here.

1293
00:43:03,418 --> 00:43:04,547
Aren't you having tteokbokki?

1294
00:43:04,548 --> 00:43:07,757
(Jong Min is still looking for tteokbokki.)

1295
00:43:07,758 --> 00:43:09,058
(Food Court)

1296
00:43:09,258 --> 00:43:11,888
Most people ate it while heading to their cars.

1297
00:43:12,088 --> 00:43:13,088
How do they eat tteokbokki while walking?

1298
00:43:13,089 --> 00:43:14,527
Can you look for someone who's eating tteokbokki?

1299
00:43:14,528 --> 00:43:16,127
Look. They're buying something.

1300
00:43:16,128 --> 00:43:18,367
- They're buying tteokbokki.
- Hurry.

1301
00:43:18,368 --> 00:43:20,427
- I was lying.
- We need to find tteokbokki...

1302
00:43:20,428 --> 00:43:22,768
- I was lying.
- What's wrong with him?

1303
00:43:22,798 --> 00:43:23,798
- Where did he go?
- Aren't you leaving...

1304
00:43:23,799 --> 00:43:24,807
for the next location?

1305
00:43:24,808 --> 00:43:27,067
- Oh, look at the tteokbokki.
- Tteokbokki.

1306
00:43:27,068 --> 00:43:28,077
(They found someone who's buying tteokbokki.)

1307
00:43:28,078 --> 00:43:30,758
Jong Min will ask you for a bite, but you shouldn't give it to him.

1308
00:43:30,938 --> 00:43:33,248
(After sabotaging Jong Min, he runs away.)

1309
00:43:33,878 --> 00:43:35,017
(DinDin left first. Could Jong Min succeed this time?)

1310
00:43:35,018 --> 00:43:36,018
Then may I...

1311
00:43:36,019 --> 00:43:37,318
(Opening his mouth)

1312
00:43:39,348 --> 00:43:41,034
(She's opening the packaging. Did she catch on right away?)

1313
00:43:41,058 --> 00:43:42,688
(Smiling happily)

1314
00:43:43,218 --> 00:43:45,258
(He's about to complete the mission.)

1315
00:43:46,428 --> 00:43:47,958
(Opening and closing his mouth)

1316
00:43:48,458 --> 00:43:50,528
(Se Yoon joined him?)

1317
00:43:51,428 --> 00:43:52,428
(Jong Min successfully completed his one-bite mission.)

1318
00:43:52,428 --> 00:43:53,428
(Opening his mouth)

1319
00:43:53,898 --> 00:43:55,297
Fried squid? Oh, my.

1320
00:43:55,298 --> 00:43:56,938
- Isn't it too big?
- Let's share it.

1321
00:43:58,568 --> 00:44:00,367
(What are they doing at the rest area in the broad daylight?)

1322
00:44:00,368 --> 00:44:01,448
(Exclaiming in disapproval)

1323
00:44:01,908 --> 00:44:03,437
(She's seeing the disgusting sight right in front of them.)

1324
00:44:03,438 --> 00:44:05,548
(Giggling)

1325
00:44:05,608 --> 00:44:07,748
- I met a fairy today.
- Thank you.

1326
00:44:08,648 --> 00:44:11,087
It was an honor for me. I'm a huge fan of yours, Jong Min.

1327
00:44:11,088 --> 00:44:12,517
Really? Thank you so much.

1328
00:44:12,518 --> 00:44:14,417
- This is a gift for you.
- Thank you.

1329
00:44:14,418 --> 00:44:15,788
- Drive safe.
- Thank you.

1330
00:44:15,858 --> 00:44:17,657
- Thank you. We'll come back.
- It was an honor.

1331
00:44:17,658 --> 00:44:18,938
- Bye.
- Oh, we won't come back.

1332
00:44:19,028 --> 00:44:20,088
Let's get going.

1333
00:44:20,488 --> 00:44:23,627
Since everyone including Jong Min succeeded, we'll give you the hint.

1334
00:44:23,628 --> 00:44:25,997
- You were the last one to succeed.
- You have to go to that location.

1335
00:44:25,998 --> 00:44:26,998
Got it.

1336
00:44:28,198 --> 00:44:29,598
What is this? What place is this?

1337
00:44:29,898 --> 00:44:31,407
That's a constellation. Let's get going for now.

1338
00:44:31,408 --> 00:44:32,607
A constellation? Is it a deer constellation?

1339
00:44:32,608 --> 00:44:34,714
There must be an astronomy museum or something like that.

1340
00:44:34,738 --> 00:44:36,614
We don't have time to stop for the restroom, right?

1341
00:44:36,638 --> 00:44:37,977
(Forget the bathroom break. They should catch up with DinDin.)

1342
00:44:37,978 --> 00:44:39,078
Let's go there for now.

1343
00:44:39,678 --> 00:44:41,177
- What is that?
- Walnut cakes.

1344
00:44:41,178 --> 00:44:42,178
(Opening his mouth)

1345
00:44:42,178 --> 00:44:43,178
What?

1346
00:44:43,179 --> 00:44:44,817
(Don't pretend you're doing a mission.)

1347
00:44:44,818 --> 00:44:46,417
Would you like a walnut cake?

1348
00:44:46,418 --> 00:44:48,718
(A lady gives him a bite.)

1349
00:44:49,018 --> 00:44:50,688
We eat so well.

1350
00:44:50,818 --> 00:44:53,028
Koreans are so friendly and caring.

1351
00:44:53,258 --> 00:44:54,628
Hello.

1352
00:44:55,698 --> 00:44:58,598
(Meanwhile, DinDin is trying to figure the hint out.)

1353
00:44:59,698 --> 00:45:03,938
(Can you figure it out?)

1354
00:45:04,238 --> 00:45:06,468
(Thinking hard)

1355
00:45:07,568 --> 00:45:09,937
There are nine sheep here. So it's Yanggu.

1356
00:45:09,938 --> 00:45:11,498
I think it's Cheomseongdae Observatory.

1357
00:45:14,578 --> 00:45:17,048
Yanggu, constellation, and astronomical observatory.

1358
00:45:17,148 --> 00:45:18,748
And astronomical observatory in Yanggu.

1359
00:45:18,788 --> 00:45:21,087
"Center of Korea Observatory."

1360
00:45:21,088 --> 00:45:22,587
(DinDin is sure that it's Yanggu.)

1361
00:45:22,588 --> 00:45:23,717
That must be the right place, right?

1362
00:45:23,718 --> 00:45:24,827
(Could it be the astronomical observatory in Yanggu?)

1363
00:45:24,828 --> 00:45:26,128
It's a one-hour drive.

1364
00:45:27,428 --> 00:45:30,298
(DinDin sets off first again.)

1365
00:45:31,058 --> 00:45:32,167
(Meanwhile, the younger members...)

1366
00:45:32,168 --> 00:45:33,168
(Sighing)

1367
00:45:33,868 --> 00:45:34,967
They won't come out.

1368
00:45:34,968 --> 00:45:36,337
(They're still waiting for the older members.)

1369
00:45:36,338 --> 00:45:38,067
We can't catch up with him even if we drive fast.

1370
00:45:38,068 --> 00:45:39,537
- We can't. How can we?
- We can't.

1371
00:45:39,538 --> 00:45:40,914
We'd be able to catch up with him if we go as far as Busan.

1372
00:45:40,938 --> 00:45:42,984
- We can't catch up with him.
- Look. DinDin is leaving now.

1373
00:45:43,008 --> 00:45:44,214
Joon, have some fun before you leave.

1374
00:45:44,238 --> 00:45:45,677
The other members haven't come yet.

1375
00:45:45,678 --> 00:45:48,078
- DinDin, don't leave yet.
- Hey, stay here a little longer.

1376
00:45:48,178 --> 00:45:50,077
DinDin, park the car.

1377
00:45:50,078 --> 00:45:51,518
- Joon.
- Yes?

1378
00:45:51,748 --> 00:45:54,188
Get out of the car and do the "Catch Catch" dance.

1379
00:45:54,688 --> 00:45:55,758
How long will you stay?

1380
00:45:56,118 --> 00:45:57,358
- Five minutes.
- Five minutes?

1381
00:45:57,458 --> 00:45:59,218
- You should definitely do it.
- I'll do it.

1382
00:45:59,658 --> 00:46:02,397
- Ready. Get set.
- I don't know

1383
00:46:02,398 --> 00:46:03,598
One, two, three, four.

1384
00:46:03,758 --> 00:46:07,028
(He's cheerleading at the rest area instead of Jamsil Baseball Stadium.)

1385
00:46:07,068 --> 00:46:08,467
That's good. Great.

1386
00:46:08,468 --> 00:46:10,988
(Mouse DinDin is satisfied. Why is the cameraman more excited?)

1387
00:46:11,568 --> 00:46:12,737
That's good. Nice.

1388
00:46:12,738 --> 00:46:14,818
(They're dancing desperately to stall Mouse DinDin.)

1389
00:46:14,878 --> 00:46:15,977
Nice. Great.

1390
00:46:15,978 --> 00:46:17,408
Why are you leaving? Hey!

1391
00:46:18,048 --> 00:46:20,678
(Why are you leaving?)

1392
00:46:21,008 --> 00:46:23,418
(I can't believe he fell for that.)

1393
00:46:23,748 --> 00:46:24,748
Hey!

1394
00:46:25,688 --> 00:46:26,688
Don't go!

1395
00:46:27,388 --> 00:46:28,657
- I danced as you asked.
- Do you know where to go?

1396
00:46:28,658 --> 00:46:29,717
I danced. I don't know!

1397
00:46:29,718 --> 00:46:31,187
- I'll tell you.
- Where is it?

1398
00:46:31,188 --> 00:46:32,748
- I'll tell you where to go.
- Tell me.

1399
00:46:32,788 --> 00:46:34,287
- Jamsil Baseball Stadium.
- Darn.

1400
00:46:34,288 --> 00:46:35,757
(He fell for it too.)

1401
00:46:35,758 --> 00:46:37,927
Hurry up. Joon, they're coming.

1402
00:46:37,928 --> 00:46:38,928
(DinDin is leaving. Fortunately, Jong Min and Se Yoon arrived.)

1403
00:46:38,929 --> 00:46:40,197
- Hurry up.
- Hurry up and get in!

1404
00:46:40,198 --> 00:46:41,918
- Hurry. What took you so long?
- Hurry up.

1405
00:46:42,268 --> 00:46:43,697
- Let's go.
- Get in. What are you waiting for?

1406
00:46:43,698 --> 00:46:44,767
Gosh, I'm full.

1407
00:46:44,768 --> 00:46:46,508
- Let's get going.
- Is everyone here?

1408
00:46:47,168 --> 00:46:48,278
- Is everyone here?
- Yes.

1409
00:46:48,538 --> 00:46:50,308
We need an address. What place is this?

1410
00:46:50,678 --> 00:46:51,918
We need to figure it out first.

1411
00:46:52,078 --> 00:46:53,247
- The address.
- Can we leave now?

1412
00:46:53,248 --> 00:46:54,678
- Please close the door.
- Okay.

1413
00:46:55,218 --> 00:46:57,377
(Looking carefully)

1414
00:46:57,378 --> 00:46:59,987
- I know where this is.
- We should figure this out.

1415
00:46:59,988 --> 00:47:01,788
- Where?
- Yeongwol.

1416
00:47:02,118 --> 00:47:03,118
Yeongwol?

1417
00:47:03,489 --> 00:47:04,026
- I know where this is.
- Where?

1418
00:47:04,027 --> 00:47:05,396
Yeongwol.

1419
00:47:05,656 --> 00:47:06,756
Yeongwol?

1420
00:47:06,856 --> 00:47:09,166
There's an astronomical observatory in Yeongwol.

1421
00:47:09,326 --> 00:47:10,465
I think he's right. Yes.

1422
00:47:10,466 --> 00:47:11,812
- Really?
- That's it. Let's leave now.

1423
00:47:11,836 --> 00:47:13,535
- It's Yeongwol.
- You just have to go straight.

1424
00:47:13,536 --> 00:47:15,236
- Okay.
- Yeongwol in Gangwon Province?

1425
00:47:15,506 --> 00:47:17,166
Go straight. That was hard.

1426
00:47:17,706 --> 00:47:19,135
What's the name of the observatory?

1427
00:47:19,136 --> 00:47:20,406
Byeolmaro Observatory.

1428
00:47:20,536 --> 00:47:21,545
"Observatory?"

1429
00:47:21,546 --> 00:47:23,682
(The two teams picked completely different locations!)

1430
00:47:23,706 --> 00:47:26,215
(Did any of the teams get it right?)

1431
00:47:26,216 --> 00:47:27,785
Those idiots.

1432
00:47:27,786 --> 00:47:29,516
(DinDin is heading to Yanggu.)

1433
00:47:29,546 --> 00:47:32,556
I want to do the shoot by myself every week.

1434
00:47:33,416 --> 00:47:34,486
I mean it.

1435
00:47:34,626 --> 00:47:37,186
Things are going so smoothly without a hitch.

1436
00:47:37,926 --> 00:47:40,125
I didn't know it could be so easy to shoot this show.

1437
00:47:40,126 --> 00:47:41,266
I had no idea.

1438
00:47:41,566 --> 00:47:44,566
Oh, right. I'd like to make a request.

1439
00:47:45,136 --> 00:47:48,335
I flew with a Korean airline on my way back to Korea.

1440
00:47:48,336 --> 00:47:51,736
They have in-flight entertainment, you know.

1441
00:47:52,036 --> 00:47:54,396
2 Days 1 Night was featured in the in-flight entertainment.

1442
00:47:54,476 --> 00:47:57,316
Judging by how well this is going, I'm definitely the star of the show.

1443
00:47:57,746 --> 00:48:00,746
But Se Yoon and Jong Min's faces took up most of the poster.

1444
00:48:00,986 --> 00:48:03,085
I didn't see any other members' faces on it.

1445
00:48:03,086 --> 00:48:05,685
And it made me a little bit upset.

1446
00:48:05,686 --> 00:48:06,686
(I'm not the star of the show?)

1447
00:48:06,687 --> 00:48:09,085
So I want only my face on the poster from now on.

1448
00:48:09,086 --> 00:48:10,086
(He wants his face to be on the poster as the lead member.)

1449
00:48:10,087 --> 00:48:13,795
Or you can put me in front, with the others in the background.

1450
00:48:13,796 --> 00:48:14,995
(DinDin is the lead member. You mean, like this?)

1451
00:48:14,996 --> 00:48:17,065
Unlike what I expected... When I met the other members...

1452
00:48:17,066 --> 00:48:18,095
(Earlier, the other members...)

1453
00:48:18,096 --> 00:48:19,866
at the rest area to play the 4-on-1 game...

1454
00:48:20,066 --> 00:48:22,536
They complained I had an advantage in that game.

1455
00:48:23,136 --> 00:48:24,136
It hurt my feelings.

1456
00:48:24,776 --> 00:48:27,575
Since the four of them teamed up to beat me...

1457
00:48:27,576 --> 00:48:28,605
(DinDin, the odd man out, is upset that he's alone.)

1458
00:48:28,606 --> 00:48:29,606
I was upset.

1459
00:48:29,646 --> 00:48:31,616
- You must feel lonely.
- I have no choice.

1460
00:48:32,476 --> 00:48:33,515
I'm going to beat them.

1461
00:48:33,516 --> 00:48:35,085
(I'll beat you guys again.)

1462
00:48:35,086 --> 00:48:36,285
What's the name of the observatory?

1463
00:48:36,286 --> 00:48:37,286
(Meanwhile, Mouse Hunters are heading to Yeongwol.)

1464
00:48:37,287 --> 00:48:38,386
Byeolmaro Observatory.

1465
00:48:38,616 --> 00:48:39,616
But it's too far.

1466
00:48:39,617 --> 00:48:40,655
(Something doesn't feel right. It's too far.)

1467
00:48:40,656 --> 00:48:41,902
- How long does it take?
- It's too far.

1468
00:48:41,926 --> 00:48:45,026
- Three hours?
- No way. That can't be.

1469
00:48:45,796 --> 00:48:47,965
We picked the wrong place. Hey, give it to me.

1470
00:48:47,966 --> 00:48:49,795
- That's not it. No way.
- Show me the hint.

1471
00:48:49,796 --> 00:48:51,842
We have to drive three hours for the next mission? That's insane.

1472
00:48:51,866 --> 00:48:53,965
But I'm sure it's Byeolmaro Observatory.

1473
00:48:53,966 --> 00:48:55,565
- Give me that.
- I visited there with Jung Hoon.

1474
00:48:55,566 --> 00:48:56,636
It's in Yeongwol?

1475
00:48:57,636 --> 00:48:58,705
Listen up. "Sa" and...

1476
00:48:58,706 --> 00:49:00,135
(Deer and sheep...)

1477
00:49:00,136 --> 00:49:01,246
"Sa" and "yang."

1478
00:49:01,776 --> 00:49:03,546
- Sayang?
- It's Yanggu.

1479
00:49:03,806 --> 00:49:04,815
Yangsa.

1480
00:49:04,816 --> 00:49:06,845
- Isn't it Yanggu?
- It's Yanggu.

1481
00:49:06,846 --> 00:49:08,492
- Isn't it Yanggu, Gangwon Province?
- There are nine sheep here.

1482
00:49:08,516 --> 00:49:11,286
(Finally, today's destination has been unveiled.)

1483
00:49:12,016 --> 00:49:15,626
(You can stargaze at the center of the Korean Peninsula.)

1484
00:49:16,626 --> 00:49:19,695
(Center of Korea Observatory in Yanggu)

1485
00:49:19,696 --> 00:49:22,065
There are nine sheep here. So it's Yanggu.

1486
00:49:22,066 --> 00:49:23,095
(9 sheep, Yanggu!)

1487
00:49:23,096 --> 00:49:24,665
(And constellation means an astronomical observatory!)

1488
00:49:24,666 --> 00:49:27,335
(DinDin's deduction was accurate.)

1489
00:49:27,336 --> 00:49:28,336
Are there nine sheep there?

1490
00:49:28,337 --> 00:49:30,705
- It's Yanggu.
- It's Yanggu.

1491
00:49:30,706 --> 00:49:33,205
- It's Yanggu.
- Had we headed to Yeongwol...

1492
00:49:33,206 --> 00:49:35,345
- We would've been in trouble.
- Right, it's Yanggu.

1493
00:49:35,346 --> 00:49:37,445
"Center of Korea Observatory?" This must be it.

1494
00:49:37,446 --> 00:49:39,515
- The observatory in Yanggu.
- Right.

1495
00:49:39,516 --> 00:49:40,516
It says 17 cars are heading there.

1496
00:49:40,517 --> 00:49:41,986
One of them must be DinDin's car.

1497
00:49:42,346 --> 00:49:43,346
(The app actually says 17 cars are heading there.)

1498
00:49:43,347 --> 00:49:45,055
Seventeen cars are heading there? That's a lot.

1499
00:49:45,056 --> 00:49:47,256
One of them must be Mouse DinDin's car.

1500
00:49:47,756 --> 00:49:48,985
We'll get there in an hour.

1501
00:49:48,986 --> 00:49:50,995
- Okay.
- I'm glad we didn't go to Yeongwol.

1502
00:49:50,996 --> 00:49:52,172
(They changed their destination from Yeongwol to Yanggu!)

1503
00:49:52,196 --> 00:49:56,066
(It's a relief they figured it out before reaching the fork.)

1504
00:49:56,496 --> 00:49:59,866
(Meanwhile, DinDin is on his way to Yanggu, beating them to it.)

1505
00:50:00,536 --> 00:50:01,765
(As things stand, DinDin has the upper hand!)

1506
00:50:01,766 --> 00:50:03,466
There's no doubt, it's Yanggu.

1507
00:50:03,806 --> 00:50:05,806
(Fidgeting)

1508
00:50:06,476 --> 00:50:08,205
(But he seems anxious for some reason.)

1509
00:50:08,206 --> 00:50:09,505
Oh, I see a small rest area there.

1510
00:50:09,506 --> 00:50:11,346
(He's looking for a small rest area?)

1511
00:50:12,316 --> 00:50:13,745
(He drank sophora root tea...)

1512
00:50:13,746 --> 00:50:15,686
(and coffee.)

1513
00:50:16,246 --> 00:50:17,985
Yes, that's right. It's a rest area.

1514
00:50:17,986 --> 00:50:20,186
(He hasn't gone to the restroom since the shoot began.)

1515
00:50:20,386 --> 00:50:23,786
(He stopped at the rest area to deal with an urgent matter.)

1516
00:50:24,596 --> 00:50:26,956
(While DinDin is gone, answering the call of nature...)

1517
00:50:27,156 --> 00:50:29,636
Did you all go to the restroom in such a short amount of time?

1518
00:50:29,866 --> 00:50:31,896
- Did you go to the restroom?
- No, I didn't.

1519
00:50:32,036 --> 00:50:34,166
- You didn't, right?
- Let's stop by the rest area.

1520
00:50:34,606 --> 00:50:35,712
We couldn't go to the restroom too.

1521
00:50:35,736 --> 00:50:38,475
- Let's drop by the rest area.
- Right, let's do that.

1522
00:50:38,476 --> 00:50:40,035
Don't you think it'd be better to catch up with DinDin...

1523
00:50:40,036 --> 00:50:42,046
instead of wasting time on restroom breaks?

1524
00:50:42,206 --> 00:50:45,015
The thing is, I feel like we keep losing by a hair.

1525
00:50:45,016 --> 00:50:46,875
- No, it's not true.
- We are far behind.

1526
00:50:46,876 --> 00:50:47,986
We're very far behind.

1527
00:50:48,046 --> 00:50:50,245
We didn't use the restroom since the opening.

1528
00:50:50,246 --> 00:50:51,786
We need to use the restroom.

1529
00:50:51,916 --> 00:50:53,955
I do want to go too.

1530
00:50:53,956 --> 00:50:55,685
But I get so competitive.

1531
00:50:55,686 --> 00:50:56,825
No, hold it.

1532
00:50:56,826 --> 00:50:57,826
(Victory over bodily urges)

1533
00:50:57,827 --> 00:50:59,155
Right, I'll hold it.

1534
00:50:59,156 --> 00:51:00,156
We'll all hold it.

1535
00:51:00,157 --> 00:51:02,425
I don't want to be defeated by him.

1536
00:51:02,426 --> 00:51:04,642
(It'll be so embarrassing if the four of us get defeated.)

1537
00:51:04,666 --> 00:51:08,306
(The two teams are getting closer as Mouse Hunters didn't stop.)

1538
00:51:09,006 --> 00:51:11,235
(Meanwhile, DinDin sets off after a quick restroom break.)

1539
00:51:11,236 --> 00:51:12,236
What's wrong?

1540
00:51:13,576 --> 00:51:16,506
(Mouse Hunters driving at full speed with fire in their eyes)

1541
00:51:16,706 --> 00:51:19,346
I wish the next mission is based on general knowledge.

1542
00:51:20,276 --> 00:51:22,686
(Mouse Hunters are fired up.)

1543
00:51:22,916 --> 00:51:25,586
We didn't even use the restroom. We should have worn diapers.

1544
00:51:26,616 --> 00:51:28,826
(What will be the result of this race?)

1545
00:51:28,926 --> 00:51:30,862
- This must be the parking lot.
- Let's get in here.

1546
00:51:30,886 --> 00:51:32,126
Block the parking lot entrance.

1547
00:51:32,426 --> 00:51:33,955
What? DinDin's van isn't here yet.

1548
00:51:33,956 --> 00:51:35,065
(Mouse Hunters got inside the parking lot.)

1549
00:51:35,066 --> 00:51:36,726
What? Did they leave already?

1550
00:51:37,796 --> 00:51:38,965
I don't see his car.

1551
00:51:38,966 --> 00:51:40,665
I don't think we got here before them.

1552
00:51:40,666 --> 00:51:42,205
We never know that.

1553
00:51:42,206 --> 00:51:43,235
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

1554
00:51:43,236 --> 00:51:44,335
Get inside.

1555
00:51:44,336 --> 00:51:46,096
You should run. You're the member that runs.

1556
00:51:46,176 --> 00:51:47,405
Hey, run!

1557
00:51:47,406 --> 00:51:48,906
(Running right away)

1558
00:51:49,076 --> 00:51:51,175
- Did he already stop by?
- What?

1559
00:51:51,176 --> 00:51:53,492
Did he already stop by and leave? I don't see DinDin's car.

1560
00:51:53,516 --> 00:51:54,815
I don't see his car too.

1561
00:51:54,816 --> 00:51:56,696
Maybe he drove inside because his car is small.

1562
00:51:57,246 --> 00:51:59,086
I really have to use the restroom.

1563
00:52:01,156 --> 00:52:02,256
Hey, the flag!

1564
00:52:03,026 --> 00:52:04,186
Grab the flag!

1565
00:52:05,556 --> 00:52:07,726
(The flag is at the entrance.)

1566
00:52:07,966 --> 00:52:09,595
- Let's go.
- What?

1567
00:52:09,596 --> 00:52:10,596
(Seon Ho running toward the flag)

1568
00:52:10,597 --> 00:52:12,536
- What is it?
- What's going on?

1569
00:52:13,066 --> 00:52:14,066
Is this it?

1570
00:52:14,067 --> 00:52:15,305
- Hey.
- This is it, right?

1571
00:52:15,306 --> 00:52:17,306
- This is the one?
- It says this is the last one.

1572
00:52:18,306 --> 00:52:21,846
"The race ends when you combine the clues hidden in the planetarium..."

1573
00:52:22,046 --> 00:52:25,276
"and claim the flag at the final destination."

1574
00:52:25,616 --> 00:52:27,115
- Where?
- Planetarium?

1575
00:52:27,116 --> 00:52:29,145
- Planetarium?
- Hello.

1576
00:52:29,146 --> 00:52:30,545
- Where is the planetarium?
- Where's the planetarium?

1577
00:52:30,546 --> 00:52:31,815
- This way.
- Thank you.

1578
00:52:31,816 --> 00:52:33,055
- Thank you.
- Right.

1579
00:52:33,056 --> 00:52:34,056
(Will they find the hint to the final destination?)

1580
00:52:34,057 --> 00:52:35,356
I still can't use the restroom.

1581
00:52:35,556 --> 00:52:36,586
What?

1582
00:52:36,786 --> 00:52:38,395
We have to find it. It's hidden somewhere here.

1583
00:52:38,396 --> 00:52:40,155
Of course, we will find it.

1584
00:52:40,156 --> 00:52:41,665
(They have to combine all the clues that are hidden at different spots.)

1585
00:52:41,666 --> 00:52:43,026
Has DinDin visited here already?

1586
00:52:43,196 --> 00:52:45,396
- No, not yet.
- He hasn't? DinDin hasn't come yet!

1587
00:52:46,236 --> 00:52:47,935
(DinDin is still on his way.)

1588
00:52:47,936 --> 00:52:49,935
- DinDin's not here yet.
- He's not here yet?

1589
00:52:49,936 --> 00:52:51,336
Yes. I asked the staff.

1590
00:52:52,306 --> 00:52:54,275
(As long as we find all the hints before he does...)

1591
00:52:54,276 --> 00:52:55,676
Hey, I see a hint here.

1592
00:52:55,776 --> 00:52:57,245
- Where?
- It's right here.

1593
00:52:57,246 --> 00:52:59,276
- It's on the floor.
- Where?

1594
00:52:59,416 --> 00:53:00,716
- This one.
- What is it?

1595
00:53:00,946 --> 00:53:02,045
It's Jong Min.

1596
00:53:02,046 --> 00:53:03,145
(Jong Min's photograph?)

1597
00:53:03,146 --> 00:53:04,485
You see the mole?

1598
00:53:04,486 --> 00:53:05,786
- Yeong Gu?
- The mole.

1599
00:53:05,816 --> 00:53:07,585
It could be somewhere here. Let's hurry.

1600
00:53:07,586 --> 00:53:08,586
- Mole.
- Where was this?

1601
00:53:08,587 --> 00:53:09,856
It was under the chair.

1602
00:53:10,386 --> 00:53:11,695
You can't show this to DinDin.

1603
00:53:11,696 --> 00:53:13,202
Of course, not. Put it in your pocket.

1604
00:53:13,226 --> 00:53:15,625
This place must be really hot and cold.

1605
00:53:15,626 --> 00:53:16,742
(DinDin has just arrived at the destination.)

1606
00:53:16,766 --> 00:53:17,896
What?

1607
00:53:19,066 --> 00:53:20,266
They are here already?

1608
00:53:22,966 --> 00:53:24,976
What? What's going on?

1609
00:53:25,506 --> 00:53:26,946
Did I take too much time for myself?

1610
00:53:28,406 --> 00:53:31,075
(Quickly getting out)

1611
00:53:31,076 --> 00:53:32,145
It's there.

1612
00:53:32,146 --> 00:53:34,022
(Running after realizing Mouse Hunters got here before him)

1613
00:53:34,046 --> 00:53:35,245
(Checking the mission)

1614
00:53:35,246 --> 00:53:36,286
What?

1615
00:53:36,946 --> 00:53:38,786
Don't show it to him. Put that in your pocket.

1616
00:53:38,816 --> 00:53:41,016
(Hey! I see a hint here.)

1617
00:53:41,056 --> 00:53:42,825
- A Korean melon.
- A Korean melon and a mole.

1618
00:53:42,826 --> 00:53:44,325
- A Korean melon.
- So this is it.

1619
00:53:44,326 --> 00:53:46,996
- Look at this. They're bowing.
- This is...

1620
00:53:47,326 --> 00:53:48,526
A Korean melon and a mole.

1621
00:53:48,796 --> 00:53:50,696
- Yeong Gu and a Korean melon.
- And a mole.

1622
00:53:50,866 --> 00:53:53,366
- Search all the seats.
- A Korean melon and Yeong Gu?

1623
00:53:55,066 --> 00:53:56,165
Is it the place?

1624
00:53:56,166 --> 00:53:58,505
(Right before DinDin bumps into Mouse Hunters)

1625
00:53:58,506 --> 00:53:59,635
A Korean melon and Yeong Gu...

1626
00:53:59,636 --> 00:54:01,875
- What's going on?
- Everyone stay quiet.

1627
00:54:01,876 --> 00:54:03,775
- What? Why?
- No, nothing.

1628
00:54:03,776 --> 00:54:04,845
We have to keep quiet here?

1629
00:54:04,846 --> 00:54:06,916
You can't hide the hints.

1630
00:54:07,746 --> 00:54:10,516
Why would you look at the ceiling? It can't be some star sign.

1631
00:54:11,116 --> 00:54:12,215
Guys, come over here.

1632
00:54:12,216 --> 00:54:14,015
(Jong Min found the fourth hint.)

1633
00:54:14,016 --> 00:54:15,586
I see another hint here.

1634
00:54:16,656 --> 00:54:19,156
(It's Jong Min again?)

1635
00:54:19,526 --> 00:54:24,196
(Current hint: Jong Min with a mole, Korean melon, a bow)

1636
00:54:25,066 --> 00:54:26,066
Get up.

1637
00:54:26,067 --> 00:54:27,235
(What is it?)

1638
00:54:27,236 --> 00:54:29,105
- Let me see it too.
- Go ahead.

1639
00:54:29,106 --> 00:54:30,106
(Is he acting cute?)

1640
00:54:30,107 --> 00:54:31,165
- What is it?
- What kind of hint is this?

1641
00:54:31,166 --> 00:54:32,476
What is it? Let me see it too.

1642
00:54:33,036 --> 00:54:35,222
(DinDin quickly realizing something as soon as he sees the image)

1643
00:54:35,246 --> 00:54:36,405
Where is it?

1644
00:54:36,406 --> 00:54:38,416
(DinDin goes to check another hint.)

1645
00:54:38,646 --> 00:54:40,575
What? It's Jong Min again.

1646
00:54:40,576 --> 00:54:42,322
(DinDin saw a photo of Jong Min with a mole.)

1647
00:54:42,346 --> 00:54:45,216
(DinDin catching up with the hints)

1648
00:54:45,356 --> 00:54:47,215
- We got the Korean melon hint.
- My voice echoes here.

1649
00:54:47,216 --> 00:54:48,825
(Using his brain to the full)

1650
00:54:48,826 --> 00:54:49,826
Okay.

1651
00:54:49,827 --> 00:54:51,427
- We still have many more hints.
- Okay.

1652
00:54:52,396 --> 00:54:54,132
- Did he get it already?
- He figured it out from that?

1653
00:54:54,156 --> 00:54:55,796
- He figured it out?
- He figured it out?

1654
00:54:55,996 --> 00:54:57,195
A Korean melon.

1655
00:54:57,196 --> 00:55:00,495
Is there something related to a belly button?

1656
00:55:00,496 --> 00:55:02,205
A belly button?

1657
00:55:02,206 --> 00:55:04,306
I think you are talking about the midway point.

1658
00:55:04,406 --> 00:55:05,476
Right, thank you.

1659
00:55:06,076 --> 00:55:07,135
(Belly button crop shirt, a Korean melon belly button, )

1660
00:55:07,136 --> 00:55:08,376
(and a belly button bow)

1661
00:55:09,006 --> 00:55:11,576
(A mole)

1662
00:55:11,876 --> 00:55:15,316
(Korea's midpoint, 38°03′10″ North latitude)

1663
00:55:15,516 --> 00:55:18,056
(Korea's belly button)

1664
00:55:18,656 --> 00:55:21,656
(The final destination of the race)

1665
00:55:21,786 --> 00:55:24,085
Jong Min's mole? A bow?

1666
00:55:24,086 --> 00:55:25,302
(Mouse Hunters must figure it out soon.)

1667
00:55:25,326 --> 00:55:27,195
- A dot?
- The place...

1668
00:55:27,196 --> 00:55:28,866
- Hey!
- What is it?

1669
00:55:29,266 --> 00:55:31,125
What's with you? I can't imagine you being smart.

1670
00:55:31,126 --> 00:55:32,595
- It's a point.
- What?

1671
00:55:32,596 --> 00:55:33,895
- A Korean melon belly button.
- What?

1672
00:55:33,896 --> 00:55:35,035
A Korean melon belly button.

1673
00:55:35,036 --> 00:55:36,736
- A belly button bow.
- Right.

1674
00:55:37,066 --> 00:55:38,305
- We have to go!
- What is it?

1675
00:55:38,306 --> 00:55:39,975
- Hold on, not yet.
- Jong Min.

1676
00:55:39,976 --> 00:55:42,346
The answer must be a belly button.

1677
00:55:42,806 --> 00:55:45,415
You must be talking about the midway point.

1678
00:55:45,416 --> 00:55:47,316
- Sorry?
- Korea's midway point.

1679
00:55:47,416 --> 00:55:48,886
- Is it over there?
- Where?

1680
00:55:49,246 --> 00:55:50,645
We have to go up?

1681
00:55:50,646 --> 00:55:52,956
Follow me and bring that.

1682
00:55:53,216 --> 00:55:55,326
We have to rush up.

1683
00:55:55,756 --> 00:55:58,225
We have to go up the mountain. Let's run!

1684
00:55:58,226 --> 00:55:59,425
(DinDin racing first)

1685
00:55:59,426 --> 00:56:02,225
- Run up the mountain!
- Seon Ho, run!

1686
00:56:02,226 --> 00:56:03,226
What?

1687
00:56:03,966 --> 00:56:06,836
(They're both checking the information sign.)

1688
00:56:07,096 --> 00:56:10,466
(It's a 20-minute walk up to the midway point.)

1689
00:56:11,336 --> 00:56:14,076
Hey, we have to go up!

1690
00:56:14,376 --> 00:56:15,976
We have to go up a long way.

1691
00:56:17,376 --> 00:56:19,646
- We'll see it up there.
- Let's go.

1692
00:56:20,516 --> 00:56:22,646
The midway point is up there.

1693
00:56:22,716 --> 00:56:24,346
There must be something on top.

1694
00:56:25,256 --> 00:56:27,785
Korea's midway point.

1695
00:56:27,786 --> 00:56:29,026
(DinDin watching Mouse Hunters)

1696
00:56:29,056 --> 00:56:30,186
It must be that way.

1697
00:56:32,726 --> 00:56:35,166
(The two teams are walking up two different ways.)

1698
00:56:35,896 --> 00:56:37,125
It's too far.

1699
00:56:37,126 --> 00:56:39,466
(From here on out, it's a matter of endurance.)

1700
00:56:40,996 --> 00:56:42,665
(DinDin's exhausted already.)

1701
00:56:42,666 --> 00:56:43,865
Let's control our pace.

1702
00:56:43,866 --> 00:56:45,175
We have to catch DinDin.

1703
00:56:45,176 --> 00:56:46,176
(Mouse Hunters entering the hiking trail)

1704
00:56:46,177 --> 00:56:47,235
Seon Ho, you should run.

1705
00:56:47,236 --> 00:56:48,956
(They're also running as fast as they can.)

1706
00:56:49,246 --> 00:56:50,375
I wish there were a restroom.

1707
00:56:50,376 --> 00:56:51,745
(They're still holding it.)

1708
00:56:51,746 --> 00:56:53,416
I can't run because I need to pee.

1709
00:56:54,216 --> 00:56:55,446
- Right?
- Gosh.

1710
00:56:58,016 --> 00:57:01,186
(It's now time to climb up.)

1711
00:57:01,526 --> 00:57:02,526
(Grunting)

1712
00:57:03,426 --> 00:57:04,455
Gosh, this is exhausting.

1713
00:57:04,456 --> 00:57:06,756
(Crying)

1714
00:57:06,856 --> 00:57:08,026
The midway point.

1715
00:57:08,396 --> 00:57:09,666
What, 500m?

1716
00:57:10,166 --> 00:57:11,395
I've only come 100m?

1717
00:57:11,396 --> 00:57:13,666
(He still has 500m to go.)

1718
00:57:14,036 --> 00:57:16,605
(Seon Ho's the only one running.)

1719
00:57:16,606 --> 00:57:18,066
Will they be able to run up?

1720
00:57:18,476 --> 00:57:20,036
I don't think they can run up.

1721
00:57:20,706 --> 00:57:22,076
This is all uphill.

1722
00:57:22,506 --> 00:57:23,646
This is crazy.

1723
00:57:24,476 --> 00:57:27,146
(Get yourself together.)

1724
00:57:27,246 --> 00:57:28,385
Okay.

1725
00:57:28,386 --> 00:57:31,615
(He sure can be smart. But he isn't fit enough.)

1726
00:57:31,616 --> 00:57:33,856
This is the toughest uphill climb I've ever done.

1727
00:57:35,486 --> 00:57:37,685
The uphill path is very steep too.

1728
00:57:37,686 --> 00:57:39,086
(DinDin's speed is getting slower.)

1729
00:57:42,166 --> 00:57:43,196
We're almost there.

1730
00:57:44,996 --> 00:57:46,166
- Hey!
- Yes.

1731
00:57:46,266 --> 00:57:47,935
- We have to go up.
- Right.

1732
00:57:47,936 --> 00:57:49,105
(Mouse Hunters are 300m away from the midway point.)

1733
00:57:49,106 --> 00:57:50,106
Here...

1734
00:57:50,736 --> 00:57:51,775
We don't know yet.

1735
00:57:51,776 --> 00:57:53,236
(We don't know the result yet.)

1736
00:57:53,406 --> 00:57:55,875
I can't even see the other guys now.

1737
00:57:55,876 --> 00:57:56,996
(Seon Ho doesn't get tired.)

1738
00:57:57,046 --> 00:57:59,446
I'm just getting ready to run whenever they're here.

1739
00:58:01,886 --> 00:58:03,215
There's such a thing as a midway point?

1740
00:58:03,216 --> 00:58:06,116
(He's 200m away.)

1741
00:58:07,716 --> 00:58:08,755
Okay, I'm almost there.

1742
00:58:08,756 --> 00:58:09,956
(Both teams are almost there.)

1743
00:58:10,686 --> 00:58:12,425
Guys, hurry up!

1744
00:58:12,426 --> 00:58:14,395
(The last showdown with both lunch and pride on the line)

1745
00:58:14,396 --> 00:58:15,666
I still have 100m to go.

1746
00:58:16,426 --> 00:58:17,526
It's too steep.

1747
00:58:18,336 --> 00:58:19,435
Gosh, it's exhausting.

1748
00:58:19,436 --> 00:58:23,206
(They'll win only when they find the midway point.)

1749
00:58:23,766 --> 00:58:26,606
(They're about to reach the midway point.)

1750
00:58:28,376 --> 00:58:32,376
(We can hear someone's breath from the midway point.)

1751
00:58:34,916 --> 00:58:37,516
(Seon Ho reached the midway point.)

1752
00:58:38,316 --> 00:58:40,586
(Will Mouse Hunters be the winners?)

1753
00:58:44,956 --> 00:58:45,996
Take it.

1754
00:58:48,966 --> 00:58:51,566
(What on earth happened?)

1755
00:58:52,266 --> 00:58:54,766
(About 2 minutes before Seon Ho arrived)

1756
00:58:55,106 --> 00:58:58,476
(DinDin reached the spot a few steps ahead of Seon Ho.)

1757
00:58:58,636 --> 00:59:01,076
I'll be lying on the ground like "The Tortoise and the Hare."

1758
00:59:01,206 --> 00:59:02,505
I'll show that the hare wins...

1759
00:59:02,506 --> 00:59:04,626
in the modern version of "The Tortoise and the Hare."

1760
00:59:05,316 --> 00:59:07,116
(The hare lying on the ground)

1761
00:59:07,816 --> 00:59:10,946
(After 2 minutes)

1762
00:59:11,816 --> 00:59:15,826
(Seon Ho reached the spot by a whisker.)

1763
00:59:15,956 --> 00:59:17,885
The tale is all a lie.

1764
00:59:17,886 --> 00:59:19,456
Don't hares lose if they take a nap?

1765
00:59:20,056 --> 00:59:21,496
My gosh, he's so annoying!

1766
00:59:22,626 --> 00:59:23,626
You are here.

1767
00:59:23,627 --> 00:59:24,695
(The annoying hare is getting on their nerves.)

1768
00:59:24,696 --> 00:59:25,895
He's so annoying.

1769
00:59:25,896 --> 00:59:28,336
- What? The race is over?
- Mouse Hunters.

1770
00:59:28,466 --> 00:59:30,965
This race had your lunch and pride on the line.

1771
00:59:30,966 --> 00:59:33,505
The race was 4 versus 1. The result of War of Idiots.

1772
00:59:33,506 --> 00:59:34,706
We didn't bet our pride.

1773
00:59:35,606 --> 00:59:37,805
- I didn't bet it at all.
- It was all about lunch.

1774
00:59:37,806 --> 00:59:38,815
Of course.

1775
00:59:38,816 --> 00:59:41,686
DinDin, the odd man out, won.

1776
00:59:42,716 --> 00:59:44,955
You have to cheer for me.

1777
00:59:44,956 --> 00:59:46,785
Why would we cheer for you when we lost?

1778
00:59:46,786 --> 00:59:49,055
But people usually cheer for you.

1779
00:59:49,056 --> 00:59:50,785
It's embarrassing when nobody does.

1780
00:59:50,786 --> 00:59:53,255
How can we cheer for you when we lost the race?

1781
00:59:53,256 --> 00:59:57,295
It was comfortable for me to carry out the missions alone.

1782
00:59:57,296 --> 00:59:59,165
It was all up to me.

1783
00:59:59,166 --> 01:00:00,196
It was so easy.

1784
01:00:00,436 --> 01:00:01,835
You see those who walked the same path?

1785
01:00:01,836 --> 01:00:05,976
For instance, Albert Einstein or Thomas Edison.

1786
01:00:06,306 --> 01:00:08,976
People like Beethoven must have been very lonely.

1787
01:00:09,476 --> 01:00:11,845
- It's not easy living as a genius.
- You...

1788
01:00:11,846 --> 01:00:13,745
- They walked the same path?
- Right, they're my seniors.

1789
01:00:13,746 --> 01:00:16,045
- Really?
- Einstein or Edison.

1790
01:00:16,046 --> 01:00:19,355
Are you joining our team or playing on your own?

1791
01:00:19,356 --> 01:00:21,585
- I won the race for lunch.
- Right, you won.

1792
01:00:21,586 --> 01:00:22,586
- Wouldn't it be faster...
- Will you...

1793
01:00:22,586 --> 01:00:23,586
- if you joined me?
- stay as a close friend?

1794
01:00:23,587 --> 01:00:25,025
I'll share my part if you join me.

1795
01:00:25,026 --> 01:00:26,525
- I'll...
- We at least...

1796
01:00:26,526 --> 01:00:27,556
Yes.

1797
01:00:27,656 --> 01:00:29,866
We at least weren't lonely.

1798
01:00:30,366 --> 01:00:31,496
What is he talking about?

1799
01:00:31,766 --> 01:00:35,066
(I'll be the tail of a mouse.)

1800
01:00:35,236 --> 01:00:37,506
The final destination you came to...

1801
01:00:38,166 --> 01:00:40,236
is the exact center of the Korean Peninsula.

1802
01:00:41,006 --> 01:00:43,206
- Of the Korean Peninsula?
- Yes.

1803
01:00:43,706 --> 01:00:47,076
(Today's destination: Yanggu, the center of the Korean Peninsula)

1804
01:00:47,446 --> 01:00:49,486
(A roofless art museum where you can feel...)

1805
01:00:49,846 --> 01:00:53,856
(Gangwon's majestic mountains along with flowers and nature)

1806
01:00:55,256 --> 01:00:57,556
(This place, which was the finish line of the race...)

1807
01:00:57,626 --> 01:01:00,456
The tower you see behind is the navel point placed...

1808
01:01:00,726 --> 01:01:02,425
at the exact center of all the farthest points...

1809
01:01:02,426 --> 01:01:04,895
of the Korean Peninsula.

1810
01:01:04,896 --> 01:01:06,166
(Navel point)

1811
01:01:06,436 --> 01:01:08,195
That's the exact midway point?

1812
01:01:08,196 --> 01:01:09,466
(He's fascinated.)

1813
01:01:09,666 --> 01:01:11,706
If you touch the navel at the center of the tower,

1814
01:01:12,376 --> 01:01:14,575
you can receive the energy of Korea's midway point.

1815
01:01:14,576 --> 01:01:15,846
- Really?
- Yes.

1816
01:01:16,276 --> 01:01:17,276
They say you get five years younger...

1817
01:01:17,277 --> 01:01:19,015
if you put your finger in the navel.

1818
01:01:19,016 --> 01:01:20,045
Put it where?

1819
01:01:20,046 --> 01:01:21,646
Put your face in the navel.

1820
01:01:21,786 --> 01:01:23,086
Here.

1821
01:01:23,716 --> 01:01:25,756
- Your face...
- Your finger...

1822
01:01:26,056 --> 01:01:27,986
- It's so cool here.
- It's really cool here.

1823
01:01:28,216 --> 01:01:29,425
At the navel point exactly at the center...

1824
01:01:29,426 --> 01:01:30,556
of the Korean Peninsula,

1825
01:01:30,686 --> 01:01:33,496
DinDin, the odd one out and the winner shouts!

1826
01:01:33,856 --> 01:01:37,095
- 2 Days 1 Night!
- 1 Night!

1827
01:01:37,096 --> 01:01:38,496
(2 Days 1 Night)

1828
01:01:40,566 --> 01:01:42,836
Now, let us use the restroom.

1829
01:01:42,966 --> 01:01:44,305
Let's climb down now.

1830
01:01:44,306 --> 01:01:45,905
- Yes.
- We've not gone to the restroom.

1831
01:01:45,906 --> 01:01:47,206
Is there no monorail?

1832
01:01:47,406 --> 01:01:50,045
Is there no restroom here? There's usually one in the mountains.

1833
01:01:50,046 --> 01:01:51,322
There usually aren't many in the mountains.

1834
01:01:51,346 --> 01:01:54,046
Right. You should carry a waste bag if you're going hiking.

1835
01:01:54,646 --> 01:01:55,945
- Seriously.
- Like a puppy?

1836
01:01:55,946 --> 01:01:57,845
We also need waste bags like puppies.

1837
01:01:57,846 --> 01:01:58,855
- To use it?
- Yes.

1838
01:01:58,856 --> 01:01:59,985
Are we heading to eat?

1839
01:01:59,986 --> 01:02:02,686
Since DinDin won...

1840
01:02:03,186 --> 01:02:04,786
Are we going to watch him eat?

1841
01:02:05,396 --> 01:02:07,326
I surely felt lonely doing it alone.

1842
01:02:07,396 --> 01:02:08,825
- Of course.
- It must have been boring.

1843
01:02:08,826 --> 01:02:10,165
Being too good can make you feel lonely.

1844
01:02:10,166 --> 01:02:11,796
Right. The world...

1845
01:02:12,066 --> 01:02:13,895
So you have to pretend you don't know.

1846
01:02:13,896 --> 01:02:16,166
- That's right.
- That's how you fit in.

1847
01:02:16,336 --> 01:02:17,865
- Goodness.
- But if you don't know anything,

1848
01:02:17,866 --> 01:02:19,836
it's hard to fit in too. Isn't that right?

1849
01:02:20,506 --> 01:02:21,675
Don't you feel lonely...

1850
01:02:21,676 --> 01:02:23,505
- They wouldn't hang out with you.
- when you don't know anything?

1851
01:02:23,506 --> 01:02:25,005
But there are four people who are clueless.

1852
01:02:25,006 --> 01:02:26,615
You have to pretend you know when you don't.

1853
01:02:26,616 --> 01:02:27,915
- "Right."
- That's right.

1854
01:02:27,916 --> 01:02:29,886
I've done that many times on shows.

1855
01:02:31,886 --> 01:02:34,956
They keep pointing out that this is Korea's midway point.

1856
01:02:35,856 --> 01:02:38,186
It's written on every sign and board everywhere.

1857
01:02:38,526 --> 01:02:39,625
That it's the center?

1858
01:02:39,626 --> 01:02:41,125
Right. Like "Midway Point Makguksu."

1859
01:02:41,126 --> 01:02:43,766
This is the midway point. Yanggu is.

1860
01:02:43,866 --> 01:02:45,026
We heard it together.

1861
01:02:47,036 --> 01:02:48,236
I missed this.

1862
01:02:48,936 --> 01:02:50,766
This frustration.

1863
01:02:51,506 --> 01:02:54,536
"They told us earlier." I missed saying that.

1864
01:02:55,406 --> 01:02:56,776
I'm hungry.

1865
01:02:57,246 --> 01:02:59,075
Do I have to activate my appetite?

1866
01:02:59,076 --> 01:03:00,315
I'm hungry.

1867
01:03:00,316 --> 01:03:01,475
(After an exciting drive, they're at the foot of the green mountains...)

1868
01:03:01,476 --> 01:03:02,786
(in Yanggu, Gangwon Province.)

1869
01:03:03,346 --> 01:03:05,716
(It's a cool, sunny place for lunch.)

1870
01:03:05,986 --> 01:03:07,986
(What menu welcomes DinDin?)

1871
01:03:09,256 --> 01:03:11,185
- It just looks good.
- I'm hungry.

1872
01:03:11,186 --> 01:03:12,525
(Juicy chicken meat coated in a special sauce)

1873
01:03:12,526 --> 01:03:14,196
- I'm so hungry.
- Gosh.

1874
01:03:14,926 --> 01:03:16,325
This is charcoal grilled dakgalbi, made with...

1875
01:03:16,326 --> 01:03:19,036
high-quality charcoal from the mountainous regions...

1876
01:03:19,236 --> 01:03:20,996
- of Gangwon Province.
- It just looks good.

1877
01:03:21,066 --> 01:03:22,136
Who will grill this?

1878
01:03:22,466 --> 01:03:24,906
- We'll grill it.
- I'll do it.

1879
01:03:25,176 --> 01:03:26,375
There are many people to do it.

1880
01:03:26,376 --> 01:03:27,606
Who'll push the chair for me?

1881
01:03:27,806 --> 01:03:29,575
- I'll push it.
- Anyone could do it.

1882
01:03:29,576 --> 01:03:31,376
(Absolute authority in front of the dakgalbi)

1883
01:03:31,676 --> 01:03:33,245
- Move. I'll do it.
- Step aside!

1884
01:03:33,246 --> 01:03:35,286
- I'm going to grill it.
- You idiot!

1885
01:03:36,716 --> 01:03:37,746
Are you done with it?

1886
01:03:38,346 --> 01:03:39,456
Yes, I am.

1887
01:03:40,516 --> 01:03:42,125
Goodness. It sounds good.

1888
01:03:42,126 --> 01:03:44,126
- It smells amazing.
- Nice.

1889
01:03:44,156 --> 01:03:46,796
What part do you like, Mouse Tail?

1890
01:03:46,856 --> 01:03:48,225
I like every part.

1891
01:03:48,226 --> 01:03:50,306
- I'll just have what's left.
- I lost to that tail.

1892
01:03:51,366 --> 01:03:53,395
- It'd be tasty.
- It smells amazing.

1893
01:03:53,396 --> 01:03:54,695
It's amazing.

1894
01:03:54,696 --> 01:03:56,006
(Looking sad)

1895
01:03:56,806 --> 01:03:58,605
I think you can start eating.

1896
01:03:58,606 --> 01:04:00,005
- A little...
- Take a look.

1897
01:04:00,006 --> 01:04:01,435
- It's not...
- You can eat this.

1898
01:04:01,436 --> 01:04:02,505
It's perfect.

1899
01:04:02,506 --> 01:04:04,146
I'll begin eating.

1900
01:04:05,316 --> 01:04:07,846
Thank you, stones.

1901
01:04:08,446 --> 01:04:10,246
Please make it sound more refined in English.

1902
01:04:10,286 --> 01:04:13,216
- Thank you, stones.
- "Thank you, stones."

1903
01:04:13,286 --> 01:04:15,156
I'll enjoy the meal, seniors!

1904
01:04:15,486 --> 01:04:17,925
This is really glossy.

1905
01:04:17,926 --> 01:04:19,806
(Taking a bite in honor of the lonely geniuses)

1906
01:04:20,196 --> 01:04:21,636
This needs to be grilled a bit more.

1907
01:04:22,326 --> 01:04:23,326
How is it?

1908
01:04:23,766 --> 01:04:24,796
It must be good.

1909
01:04:25,236 --> 01:04:26,696
It can't be bad.

1910
01:04:26,796 --> 01:04:29,205
- Doesn't it smell?
- It's the taste you know.

1911
01:04:29,206 --> 01:04:31,066
- Right.
- It's so good.

1912
01:04:31,876 --> 01:04:33,505
I'd eat a bowl of rice with this.

1913
01:04:33,506 --> 01:04:35,605
(Even Light Eater DinDin can't resist eating it.)

1914
01:04:35,606 --> 01:04:37,576
It smells amazing.

1915
01:04:37,676 --> 01:04:39,076
Let's quickly move on.

1916
01:04:39,476 --> 01:04:41,615
DinDin also doesn't want to eat alone.

1917
01:04:41,616 --> 01:04:43,816
- He also knows.
- He's lonely.

1918
01:04:44,086 --> 01:04:45,716
There aren't many scenes to use.

1919
01:04:46,916 --> 01:04:48,055
He's not eating so much.

1920
01:04:48,056 --> 01:04:49,886
How long are you going to keep filming this?

1921
01:04:50,356 --> 01:04:51,826
- Thank you!
- You're welcome.

1922
01:04:52,496 --> 01:04:54,225
- Thank you for the food.
- The kimchi looks good.

1923
01:04:54,226 --> 01:04:55,706
Try the kimchi. Tell us if it's good.

1924
01:04:56,466 --> 01:04:58,295
(Spicy and mouthwatering aged kimchi)

1925
01:04:58,296 --> 01:04:59,296
It aged well.

1926
01:04:59,297 --> 01:05:00,936
(Spicy and mouthwatering aged kimchi)

1927
01:05:01,766 --> 01:05:02,766
Go ahead.

1928
01:05:03,136 --> 01:05:04,766
This isn't the end, DinDin.

1929
01:05:05,136 --> 01:05:07,036
You should also try the makguksu.

1930
01:05:07,806 --> 01:05:08,946
We'll bring it in.

1931
01:05:10,476 --> 01:05:14,316
